$ Perl module ExtUtils::MakeMaker
@ ExtUtils::MakeMaker

code {
use ExtUtils::MakeMaker;

WriteMakefile(
    NAME            => 'Foo::Bar::Baz.pm',
    VERSION_FROM    => 'lib/Foo/Bar/Baz.pm'
);
code }


Apparently, `Module::Build` is an alternative to `ExtUtils::MakeMaker`.

{ MANIFEST.SKIP

File containing regular expressions that match files that need to be excluded from MANIFEST and hence from the
distributed file:
code {
\.git
\.swp$
Foo-Bar-.*\.tar\.gz
blib
README.md
MANIFEST\.bak$
Makefile$
Makefile.old
code }

}

